<title>Machaut: Le Rem&egrave;de de Fortune</title>
</head><body>
<h2>Le Rem&egrave;de de Fortune</h2>

<dl>
<dt>Guillaume de Machaut</dt>
<dd>Le Rem&egrave;de de Fortune<br>
Marc Mauillon, Pierre Hamon, et al.<br>
<i>Eloquentia EL0918</i> [CDx2]</dd>
</dl>

<h3>Contents:</h3>
<p><ol>
<h4>Guillaume de Machaut: Le Rem&egrave;de de Fortune<br>
CD-1</h4>
<li>Lay: Qui n'aroit autre deport</li>
<li>Complainte: Tieus rit au main qui au soir pleure</li>

<h4>CD-2</h4>
<li>Chant Roial: Joye, plaisance, et douce nourreture</li>
<li>Balladelle: En amer a douce vie</li>
<li>Balade: Dame, de qui toute ma joie vient</li>
<li>Chanson Balad&eacute;e: Dame, a vous sans retollir</li>
<li>Rondelet: Dame, mon cuer en vous remaint (M. Mauillon, Biffi,
Hamon)</li>
<li>Rondelet: Dame, mon cuer en vous remaint (M. Mauillon, Biffi,
Goubiaud)</li>
</ol></p>

<P><B>Performers:</B><br>
Marc Mauillon (voice), VivaBiancaLuna Biffi (voice, fiddle),
Ang&eacute;lique Mauillon (gothic harp), Pierre Hamon (flutes,
drums)<br>
with Serge Goubioud (voice), Emmanuel Vistorky (voice)<br>
Pierre Hamon, director
</p>

<P><B>Playing time:</B> 68" 14' + 24' 48" = 1h 33' 02"
</P>

<P><B>Recording site and date:</B><BR>
Chapelle Jesus enfant, Paris, France [11/2008];<br>
Rel.: 2009</P>

<p><strong>Reviewed in:</strong><br>
Diapason (#-p.): 572-106 (Sept. 2009)<br>
Fanfare (Vol./#-p.): 33/5-315 (May/June 2010)<br>
Gramophone (Vol./#-p.): 97/1051-95 (Nov. 2009)
</p>

<p><strong>Comments:</strong><br>
Information from CD.<br>
Jerome F. Weber wrote in Fanfare:<br>
There is an Easter egg here, a second performance of the rondelet
for unaccompanied voices not indicated in the printed contents.
The timing of track 5 in the booklet is incorrect, and there is no
indication of 35 seconds of silence before track 6 begins.
</P>

